        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 7 at 12:47PM EDT by NWS Wakefield VA</headline>
        <description>At 1247 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Littleton, or 13 miles west of Roanoke Rapids, moving northeast at 55
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Barley around 1255 PM EDT.
Emporia around 110 PM EDT.
Green Plain around 115 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Ante, Brink, Adams
Grove, Gray, Grizzard, Gum Forks, Triplet, Lanes Corner, Henrico, and
Vultare.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Heavy rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
